<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-08-03T09:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-08-03T09:30:00-05:00" n="929" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d929">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7331A15/23: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-03T10:00:00-04:30">August 3, 1929—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:30 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>112. Department’s telegram No. 16, May 17, 5 p.m., and Legation’s
                            despatch No. 1860, May 19th.</p>
                        <p>Although I have repeatedly assisted the company informally, I feel they
                            have reached an impasse and have advised them to confer with the
                            Department as to what further action, if any, the Legation could
                            properly take.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>